<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Watford striker Danny Welbeck is attracting interest from Southampton and Crystal Palace. </p>

<p>The Selhurst Park club are also considering a move for QPR winger Bright Samuel after signing his teammate Ebere Eze for £19.5m last week.</p>

<p>Watford are discussing a possible deal to re-sign Fernando Forestieri.</p>

<p>Watford striker Danny Welbeck is attracting interest from Southampton and Crystal Palace</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Liverpool are prepared to match Watford’s £40million asking price for striker Ismaila Sarr.</p>

<p>The 22-year-old is said to be Jurgen Klopp’s top transfer target this summer as he looks to reinforce his bench with Sadio Mane, Roberto Firmino and Mo Salah nailed-on starters.</p>

<p>Sarr has risen to the top of Liverpool's wishlist because of his ability to play on either the wing or through the middle - making him a more attractive proposition to Wolves star Adam Traore, according to the Sun.</p>

